<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1868,2037]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1868,1893]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Costal margin basally sinuate, distally rather evenly curved into apical margin. RA gradually converging to margin, 
<emphasis box="[329,348,1906,1929]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">ir</emphasis>
absent. 
<collectingCountry box="[449,483,1905,1928]" name="Poland" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">RP</collectingCountry>
simple. Basal cell distinct. MP forked deeper than MA and/or 
<number box="[1238,1250,1904,1928]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="3.0">3</number>
-branched. CuA elbowed at apex of basal cell. CuA 
<number box="[550,563,1940,1964]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="2.0">2</number>
simple, rarely forked. Pcu subparallel to CuP. Commissural margin carinate. Surface punctate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
